HR NO. 278 ENROLLED
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request the Louisiana Department of Justice
to conduct a comprehensive review of the statutory framework and administrative
procedures relative to electronic monitoring in this state and to receive feedback and input
from relevant stakeholders to identify efficiencies, deficiencies, and conflicts within the
existing statutory framework that governs electronic monitoring providers and practices.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that in conducting this review, the Louisiana
Department of Justice shall include consideration of all of the following:
(1) Identification of current efficiencies, deficiencies, and potential conflicts in
existing statutes and administrative rules relative to electronic monitoring.
(2) Analysis of the electronic monitoring laws of other states, with a focus on
methods for permitting, fee structures, and the frequency of inspections.
(3) Development of recommendations for a comprehensive system of registration
and oversight to ensure all electronic monitoring providers operating in this state meet
rigorous technical and reporting standards.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Louisiana Department of Justice may receive
testimony, feedback, input, and data from all of the following:
(1) The Louisiana Sheriffs' Association.
(2) The Louisiana District Attorneys Association.
(3) The Department of Public Safety and Corrections, including the offices of
probation and parole and juvenile justice.
(4) The Louisiana Commission on Law Enforcement and Administration of Criminal
Justice.
(5) The office of the state public defender.
(6) Representatives of the electronic monitoring provider industry.
(7) Any other relevant stakeholders.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Louisiana Department of Justice shall submit
a written report of its findings and recommendations to the House Committee on
Administration of Criminal Justice no later than sixty days prior to the start of the 2027
Regular Session of the Legislature of Louisiana.
